     docs: rtk privacy-posture audit + retention reduction (90d -> 14d)

     Followup to PR #40's deferred privacy review of RTK
     (https://github.com/rtk-ai/rtk) at version 0.38.0.

     Findings (full report: docs/archive/audit/rtk-privacy-posture-2026-
     04-30.md):

     - Network exfiltration: NEGLIGIBLE. Telemetry is OFF by default
       and the v0.38.0 binary contains no collection endpoint (literal
       string in binary: "no telemetry endpoint configured"). Static-
       string scan turned up no posthog/sentry/datadog/amplitude
       markers; only documentation URLs are present.
     - Local plaintext command history: every command's full text +
       arguments + absolute project path is logged to
       ~/.local/share/rtk/history.db (SQLite). Default retention was
       90 days. Threat-model equivalent: ~/.bash_history.
     - Cross-project visibility in a single DB: history aggregates
       across all RTK-enabled projects.

     Mitigations applied:
     1. Retention shortened from 90 days to 14 days. Edited locally in
        ~/.config/rtk/config.toml — out of repo scope, but documented in
        the audit report's "Mitigations applied in this PR" section so
        future operators know the choice was deliberate.
     2. CLAUDE.md "Tool Output Compression (RTK)" section now carries
        a Privacy posture sub-section with audit summary, re-audit
        triggers, defense-in-depth env var, and ongoing-hygiene checks.
     3. Audit report committed under docs/archive/audit/ for the
        permanent record.

